<paragraph id="2D02FD0E7630420DB99629CDFB119716" blockId="6.[166,1225,404,624]" pageId="6" pageNumber="373">
Remarks. Male specimen was identiFIed by C. Pisică as 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D7630420DBA2629CCF9899496" authority="(Fabricius, 1775) (Banchinae)" authorityName="Banchinae" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Glypta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mensurator">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C7630420DBA2629CCFC4994A8" box="[875,1094,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="373">Glypta mensurator</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1775) (Banchinae)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<specimenCount id="3BBB36877630420DB88129ADFA5D9496" box="[460,594,469,496]" pageId="6" pageNumber="373" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen was identiFIed by C. Pisică as 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D7630420DBD1529ACF9E59776" authority="(Gravenhorst, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zaglyptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varipes">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C7630420DBD1529ACF8F79768" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="373">Zaglyptus varipes</emphasis>
(Gravenhorst, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
.According to key provided by M. Fitton and co-authors (1988) 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D7630420DB9EB2A6DF9159748" authorityName="Fitton, Shaw &amp; Gauld" authorityYear="1988" box="[166,282,533,558]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vexator">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C7630420DB9EB2A6DF9159748" box="[166,282,533,558]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="373">P. vexator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has similar coloration with 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D7630420DBB172A6DFAD69748" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1829" box="[602,729,532,558]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberosa">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C7630420DBB172A6DFAD69748" box="[602,729,532,558]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="373">P. tuberosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having unbanded subbasally hind tibiae and complete pleural carina (as in 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D7630420DBB8C2A4DFB229729" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1829" box="[705,813,565,591]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C7630420DBB8C2A4DFB229729" box="[705,813,565,591]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="373">P. rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Additionally, all the three species differ in sculpture of metasomal tergites II–IV (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B7630420DBB9D2A2DFB019716" box="[720,782,597,624]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1005,1027]" captionTargetBox="[259,1136,176,991]" captionTargetId="figure-342@5.[259,1136,175,991]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Polysphincta, ♀. 1–2 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — P. tuberosa; 2 — P. vexator; 3–5 — metasoma (dorsal view): 3 — P. tuberosa, tergites III–IV; 4 — P. rufipes, tergites II–IV; 5 — P. vexator, tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449479/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="373">FIg. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
